    <title>Frequently Asked Questions - Resumeforge</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Get answers to frequently asked questions about Resumeforge. Learn about pricing, features, compatibility, and more.">
    
    <!-- JSON-LD Schema for FAQPage -->
    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q1: How much does ResumeForge cost and is there a free version?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ResumeForge offers four plans: Free (1 resume, 3 templates, basic AI suggestions), Premium ($9.99/month or $59.88/year, unlimited resumes, all 50+ templates, AI writer, ATS optimization), Professional ($19.99/month, cover letter generator, LinkedIn optimizer, interview prep), and Lifetime ($199 one-time, all features forever). All paid plans include a 7-day free trial. | Feature | Free | Premium | Professional | Lifetime | |---------|------|---------|--------------|----------| | Resumes | 1 | Unlimited | Unlimited | Unlimited | | Templates | 3 | 50+ | 50+ | 50+ | | AI Content | Basic | Advanced | Advanced | Advanced | | ATS Check | — | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | | Cover Letters | — | — | ✓ | ✓ | | Price | $0 | $9.99/mo | $19.99/mo | $199 once | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q2: What AI features does ResumeForge offer to improve my resume?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ResumeForge's AI rewrites bullet points for impact (action verb + result + metric), optimizes for ATS keywords, suggests skills based on your target role, generates professional summaries, identifies and fixes weak phrasing, and provides a \"Resume Score\" with specific improvement suggestions. The AI was trained on 10 million successful resumes and 50,000+ job descriptions. - **Bullet Point Rewriter:** Transforms \"Responsible for managing team\" → \"Led 12-person engineering team to deliver $2M revenue project 3 weeks ahead of schedule\" - **ATS Keyword Optimizer:** Scans job description and inserts missing high-value keywords naturally - **Skills Suggestion Engine:** Recommends skills based on your experience and target role (95% accuracy validated by hiring managers) - **Professional Summary Generator:** Creates 3 summary options tailored to career level and industry - **Resume Score:** 0–100 score with actionable fixes (formatting, keywords, completeness, impact) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q3: How do I create an ATS-optimized resume with ResumeForge?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Select the \"ATS Optimizer\" tab, paste your target job description, and click \"Analyze.\" ResumeForge identifies missing keywords, suggests optimal resume section ordering, flags formatting issues that confuse ATS software, and rewrites your content to match. The system supports 40+ ATS platforms including Workday, Greenhouse, Lever, and Taleo. 1. **Paste job description** into the ATS Optimizer 2. **Review keyword gaps** highlighted in red (missing) and green (present) 3. **Click \"Optimize\"** — AI naturally integrates missing keywords 4. **Check ATS preview** — see exactly how your resume appears to ATS software 5. **Export as .docx or plain-text PDF** (both ATS-friendly) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q4: Which file formats can I export my resume to and are they ATS-friendly?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "ResumeForge exports to ATS-optimized PDF, .docx (editable in Word), plain text, and a dedicated LinkedIn PDF format. All exports preserve formatting across devices and are tested against 40+ ATS platforms. Premium users can also generate a shareable web link and QR code for digital applications. | Format | ATS-Friendly | Best For | Editable | |--------|-------------|----------|----------| | PDF (ATS-optimized) | ✓ | Most applications | No | | .docx | ✓ | Applications requesting Word format | Yes | | Plain text | ✓ | Paste into online forms | Yes | | LinkedIn PDF | ✓ | LinkedIn \"Featured\" section | No | | Web link | N/A | Portfolio, email signature | N/A | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q5: Is my resume data secure and private on ResumeForge?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. ResumeForge is SOC 2 Type II certified, GDPR compliant, and never sells your data. Your resume content is encrypted at rest (AES-256) and in transit (TLS 1.3). We do not use your resume data to train AI models. You can delete your account and all data permanently at any time with one click. - SOC 2 Type II certified (annual independent audit) - GDPR compliant (EU users have full data portability and deletion rights) - CCPA compliant (California users) - No data resale or sharing with recruiters (contractually guaranteed) - Optional: local-only mode (data never leaves your device, available on Professional plan) ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q6: Can I use ResumeForge on mobile devices and which browsers are supported?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. ResumeForge works on all modern browsers (Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge) and has a dedicated iOS app (Android coming Q3 2025). The mobile interface is fully featured—you can create, edit, and export resumes from your phone. An internet connection is required; offline mode is roadmapped for late 2025. | Device | Supported | Notes | |--------|-----------|-------| | Windows (Chrome/Edge) | ✓ | Full feature parity | | macOS (Safari/Chrome) | ✓ | Full feature parity | | iPad | ✓ | Optimized tablet layout | | iPhone | ✓ | Dedicated iOS app | | Android | Beta | Web version functional | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q7: Does ResumeForge integrate with job search platforms and LinkedIn?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. ResumeForge integrates with LinkedIn (one-click profile import and export), Indeed, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter, and 15+ job boards. The Chrome extension lets you auto-fill application forms with one click. Premium users get \"Auto-Apply\" that submits tailored applications to matched jobs (review required before sending). - **Import:** LinkedIn profile → resume draft (2 seconds) - **Export:** Resume → LinkedIn PDF / Featured section - **Job Boards:** Indeed, Glassdoor, ZipRecruiter, Monster, CareerBuilder - **Browser Extension:** Auto-fill application forms on 100+ job sites - **Calendar:** Sync interviews with Google Calendar / Outlook ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q8: How accurate and effective are ResumeForge's AI suggestions?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In a 2024 study of 5,000 ResumeForge users, those who applied AI suggestions saw a 68% increase in interview invitations. The AI's bullet point rewrites are validated by 200+ professional recruiters. ResumeForge achieves 94% accuracy in ATS keyword matching and a 4.7/5 user satisfaction rating for AI-generated content quality. - Interview invitation increase: +68% (average across 5,000 users) - ATS keyword match accuracy: 94% - Recruiter-rated bullet point quality: 4.6/5 - User satisfaction (AI suggestions): 4.7/5 - False positive rate (incorrect suggestions): <3% ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q9: What customer support does ResumeForge provide?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Free users get email support (48-hour response) and knowledge base access. Premium users receive priority email (12-hour response) and live chat. Professional users get phone support, 1-on-1 resume reviews by career experts, and a 30-minute onboarding call. All users can access 60+ video tutorials and weekly career webinars. | Support Type | Free | Premium | Professional | |--------------|------|---------|--------------| | Email support | ✓ (48hr) | ✓ (12hr) | ✓ (4hr) | | Live chat | — | ✓ | ✓ | | Phone support | — | — | ✓ | | 1-on-1 review | — | — | ✓ | | Onboarding call | — | — | ✓ | ---"
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Q10: How do I cancel my ResumeForge subscription?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Cancel anytime from Account Settings—no phone call needed. Monthly plans stop billing immediately and remain active until period end. Annual plans have a 30-day money-back guarantee (full refund, no questions). Lifetime plan users can request a refund within 60 days. Your data is saved for 6 months if you want to reactivate. - **Monthly:** Cancel anytime; access until month-end; no refund (unused time not billable) - **Annual:** Full refund within 30 days; after 30 days, access continues until year-end - **Lifetime:** Full refund within 60 days (no questions asked) - **Data retention:** Account inactive but restorable for 6 months; hard delete after 12 months ---"
      }
    }
  ]
}
